 Syntax:  .wwipe <parameter>

Results:  Wipes the messages from the wizards board.
          .wwipe <NUM> <NUM> where both number are the same is a line delete.
          UNLIKE .cmail or .csent, you will NOT be asked to verify the    
          wipe. 
          
Example:
   To wipe all messages from the board, type            : .wwipe all
   To clear the first line type                         : .wwipe          
   To clear line 10 from the board, type                : .wwipe 10        
   To clear all lines from the beginning to line 5, type: .wwipe to 5        
   To clear all lines from line 8 to the end, type      : .wwipe from 8      
   To clear all lines from line 8 to line 10, type      : .wwipe from 8 to 10
   To clear all lines except line 4, type               : .wwipe except 4     
   To clear all lines except line 4 through 9, type     : .wwipe except 4 to 9

See also: wipe, gwipe, swipe, wnote
